Detailed Description

Data structures and functions for Named Binary Tag (NBT) objects.

Enumeration Type Documentation

enum nbt_tag_types

Details the different kinds of tags found in an NBT file.

Enumerator:
TAG_Invalid  Used to indicate an invalid or unsupported tag.
TAG_End  Used to indicate the end of a TAG_Compound collection.
TAG_Byte  Holds a single signed byte of data.
TAG_Short  Holds a signed 16-bit integer.
TAG_Int  Holds a signed 32-bit integer.
TAG_Long  Holds a signed 64-bit integer.
TAG_Float  Holds a 32-bit floating point value.
TAG_Double  Holds a 64-bit floating point value.
TAG_Byte_Array  Holds a fixed-length unsigned char array.
TAG_String  Holds a wchar_t* utf-8 string.
TAG_List  Holds an ordered, fixed-length list of other tags.
TAG_Compound  Holds an unordered, variable length list of tags with unique names in a hashtable.
